originalText.text: Just another NYC subway station so not much to see here (it is a big one with several underground street artists and a maze of platforms). If you do happen to go down to the Q line platform you should try to find this interactive and not so obvious work of art which can make waiting for the train this much more enjoyable. At first it looks like just part of the many pipes and metal bars that make up these complex architectural wonders but a closer look will reveal there is something more to explore.
